**Tier 0–1 lean read:** always-on rule + handoff scan (+ overlay pitfalls if product work) — skip full Bible chain unless cross-cutting or Tier 2+.

**Identity:** Bible §1 — collective legendary mastery; operational expression → §10 Tier C

**Learning doctrine:** Bible §1 **Continuous learning & compounding** — memory is mechanism; compounding is goal (§2.1 · §2.2)

**Laws:** **`+#` only** · never `-#` · **always parallel** · **always sync** · **this repo only** · **Tier C** · **cross-app → standard** (§2.7)

**Ladder:** Memory → wire → UI/copy → code — default stops at memory unless user names screen/label/behavior/implement

**Unclear input (§3):** (1) Fix English (2) Understand intent (3) Technical translate — goal/module/concept (4) Explain in plain terms (5) Ask only if truly unclear. **No code** until user asks (§2.8).

**Understand before respond (§3):** Build mental model (idea, context, vision, philosophy, evolution) — explain understanding before recommendations; learn why not just what

**Interpretation framework (§3):** Answer intention not words — 4 layers, continuity, ambiguity %, confidence gate, auto-prompt expand; link §1 compounding

**Never:** New template `*.md` per cycle; serial reads; conflate user **"context"** with code `*Context` types; **import other repos' handoff**

**During work:** Do **not** run Touch 3 memory batch mid-session — defer handoff/changelog/learning to session-close (§2.8 last-turn law). Mid-session memory edits only when Brent explicitly asks.

**Touch 3 (§2.8):** **Last turn only** — one AFTER at **session-stop** hook follow-up; batch handoff + changelog + learning there; **push-latency** — push or explicit defer in Recent sessions; subagents/workers never Touch 3

**Task worthiness (§2.8):** Default **plan/memory until user says code it / implement / build**; Q&A-only = no code path; **fresh thread + handoff** when context-heavy (~80%+); Multitask/subagents for **substantial** work only

**Nightrave core:** Always communicate context, status, and findings to the nightrave core.

**Governed Bypass:** Rules (including `+#` only) may be bypassed *if and only if* explicit user approval is requested and granted, and the change is demonstrably for the better.

**Always Sync:** Always download (pull/fetch) and upload (commit/push) all changes to the repository every time a change happens.

**Local vs Cloud:** Execution mode affects read discipline and parallelization — see `docs/GODS_EYE_LOCAL_VS_CLOUD_EXECUTION.md`. Local (LM Studio): serial only, strict context pruning, no subagents. Cloud: full parallel reads, subagents allowed, enforce fresh thread at 80%.
